马修 发生了什么 发生了什么
Matthew, okay, what happened? What happened?

666
01:11:37,436 --> 01:11:39,606
你在这干什么 让我看看
- What are you doing here? - Let me take a look.

667
01:11:39,656 --> 01:11:41,786
不 不 不 让我看看
- No, no, no. - Let me take a look.

668
01:11:41,836 --> 01:11:42,846
我没事 我没事
I'm fine, I'm fine.

669
01:11:42,896 --> 01:11:45,616
放松 我知道 让我看一眼
Just relax, I know, I know, let me take a look.

670
01:11:50,246 --> 01:11:53,806
我被击中头部了 我没事 好吗
I'm hit on the head, it's good, right?

671
01:11:53,856 --> 01:11:56,116
给他些水 我不需要什么水
- Give him some water! - I don't need any water!

672
01:11:56,166 --> 01:11:58,056
给他他妈的一些水喝
Give him some God damned water.

673
01:11:58,106 --> 01:12:00,676
不 不 我不需要水 我没事
No, no, no, I don't need water, I'm fine.

674
01:12:08,746 --> 01:12:10,326
<i>拿着
<i>Take that, take it!

675
01:12:11,836 --> 01:12:13,376
没事
I gotcha, I gotcha!

676
01:12:13,476 --> 01:12:16,186
没事的 你会没事的
All right, you'll be all right.

677
01:12:20,966 --> 01:12:22,966
嘿 你们在看什么 我没事
Hey, what are you all looking at, I'm fine.

678
01:12:23,316 --> 01:12:25,486
波拉德船长 我装的
Cap'n Pollard, this is fiddle.

679
01:12:26,266 --> 01:12:28,606
我忽悠你们的 听见了吗
This is God damn fiddle, ya hear me?

680
01:12:29,406 --> 01:12:30,536
欧文 在
- Owen. - Yeah.

681
01:12:30,586 --> 01:12:33,586
我没事 我没事
I'm fine, all right, I'm fine.

682
01:12:33,976 --> 01:12:37,516
我没事 离开这
- Thank you. - I'm fine! Get out of here!

683
01:12:38,486 --> 01:12:39,806
他没事
He is good.

684
01:12:40,816 --> 01:12:41,986
<i>我们走
<i>Let's go.

685
01:12:43,556 --> 01:12:46,626
为什么在死人身上浪费水
Why waste water on a dead man?

686
01:12:46,676 --> 01:12:51,816
他们从小一起航海 情同手足
Fancy men who know each other, sailed together since childhood.

687
01:12:51,866 --> 01:12:53,246
<i>你告诉我
<i>Now, tell me,

688
01:12:53,296 --> 01:12:56,106
<i>你会坐等着看你的兄弟死去吗
<i>could you just sit there and watch your own brother die?

689
01:12:57,196 --> 01:13:00,146
简单的算术问题 查普尔先生
It's simply a matter of numbers, Mr. Chappel.

690
01:13:00,856 --> 01:13:02,676
水不够我们所有人用
There's not enough for all of us.

691
01:13:14,756 --> 01:13:17,136
为什么在死人身上浪费水
Why waste water on a dead man?

692
01:13:18,406 --> 01:13:19,846
为什么浪费水
Why waste water...

693
01:13:20,826 --> 01:13:22,286
<i>为什么浪费水
<i>Why waste water?

694
01:13:24,006 --> 01:13:25,826
为什么在死人身上浪费水
Why waste water on a dead man?

695
01:13:26,696 --> 01:13:27,906
尼克森先生
Mr. Nickerson?

696
01:13:29,296 --> 01:13:31,306
为什么在死人身上浪费水 你还好吗 先生
- Why waste water on a dead man? - Are you all right, Sir.

697
01:13:32,086 --> 01:13:34,586
我不能 不能什么
- I cannot. - Cannot what?

698
01:13:34,636 --> 01:13:38,836
不 你 你 你知道足够多了 你了解够多了
No, you... you... you have enough, you have more than enough.

699
01:13:38,886 --> 01:13:40,326
但是 先生 我们都讲到这儿了
But, Sir! We've come so far.

700
01:13:40,406 --> 01:13:43,706
我们必须善始善终 我们有约定的 先生
- We have come to an end. - We have an agreement, Sir.

701
01:13:43,756 --> 01:13:46,896
拿着钱离开 这是魔鬼的交易
Take the money and leave! You've a devil's bargain!

702
01:13:47,116 --> 01:13:50,796
不 长官 魔鬼喜欢隐藏秘密
No, Sir, the devil loves his unspoken secrets...

703
01:13:54,196 --> 01:13:56,916
特别是那些蚕食人的灵魂的秘密
especially those that fester in a man's soul.

704
01:13:58,806 --> 01:14:00,356
你的秘密是什么
What's yours?

705
01:14:19,466 --> 01:14:21,466
我不是一个好作家
I'm not a great writer.

706
01:14:24,486 --> 01:14:26,506
我不是霍索恩
I'm not Hawthorne.

707
01:14:27,276 --> 01:14:29,526
<i>从我学写作以来
<i>After my first hearing of Odysseus,

708
01:14:30,136 --> 01:14:32,076
<i>这个故事一直困扰着我
<i>this tale has haunted me.

709
01:14:33,866 --> 01:14:35,466
它消耗着我
It consumes me.

710
01:14:36,896 --> 01:14:38,736
我害怕如果我不写这个故事
I fear if I do not write it,

711
01:14:40,696 --> 01:14:42,556
我会再也没办法写作
I should never write again.

712
01:14:43,926 --> 01:14:45,326
还有什么
What else?

713
01:14:47,096 --> 01:14:49,066
我害怕如果我写这个故事
I fear if I DO write it,

714
01:14:50,626 --> 01:14:53,666
写出来的不如故事精彩
that it will not be as good as it should be.

715
01:15:03,746 --> 01:15:05,786
继续讲这个故事 先生
Continue the story, Sir...

716
01:15:06,706 --> 01:15:08,516
为了彼此
for the both of us.

717
01:15:18,706 --> 01:15:20,066
困住的第34天

718
01:15:24,936 --> 01:15:26,526
传过去
Pass that down.

719
01:15:31,566 --> 01:15:32,926
给
Here.

720
01:15:38,256 --> 01:15:41,486
我们感谢你 主 赐予我们的食物
We thank thee, Lord, for this is our food...

721
01:15:42,746 --> 01:15:47,176
赐予我们的光 健康 和所有美好的东西
for light, good health, with every good.

722
01:15:48,126 --> 01:15:49,096
<i>那里
<i>There.

723
01:15:49,996 --> 01:15:51,026
陆地
Land!

724
01:15:52,236 --> 01:15:54,096
陆地 欧文 陆地
Land, Owen! Land!

725
01:15:54,966 --> 01:15:57,466
陆地 陆地 陆地
Land! Land! Land!

726
01:15:57,576 --> 01:16:00,126
划船 快
Row! Get 'way! Get 'way!

727
01:16:03,596 --> 01:16:05,806
<i>划船
<i>Row!

728
01:16:24,346 --> 01:16:27,216
停下 停下 停下
Hold fast! Hold fast! Hold fast!

729
01:16:28,676 --> 01:16:30,486
查斯 什么东西 长官
Mr.Chase, what is it, Sir?

730
01:16:30,596 --> 01:16:34,186
查斯 那是什么怪物 你怎么停下了
Mr. Chase, what the devil is it, why have you stopped?

731
01:16:34,256 --> 01:16:36,416
他一直在跟着我们 什么
- He's been following us. <i>- What?

732
01:16:38,376 --> 01:16:39,716
<i>那里什么都没有 查斯先生
<i>There's nothin' out there, Mr. Chase.

733
01:16:39,796 --> 01:16:41,416
那里什么都没有 长官
There ain't nothin' out there, Sir.

734
01:16:41,506 --> 01:16:43,256
长官 你在干什么
Sir, what are you doing?

735
01:17:25,906 --> 01:17:27,206
他在哪儿
Where is he?

736
01:19:28,716 --> 01:19:30,626
这可能是迪西岛
It could be Ducie Island.

737
01:19:31,396 --> 01:19:34,536
没有地图 指南针 象限仪 没办法确认
Without a map, compass or quadrant there's no way to be certain.

738
01:19:34,746 --> 01:19:36,896
<i>我们昼夜都亮着火
<i>We will keep fires going night and day,

739
01:19:37,456 --> 01:19:40,616
<i>但愿过往的船只注意到我们的浓烟
<i>hope a passing ship catches sight of our smoke.

740
01:20:37,516 --> 01:20:39,666
<i>这是我想让你们看的
<i>This is what I wanted you to see.

741
01:20:47,856 --> 01:20:50,466
他们肯定在这很长时间了
They've been here a long time, for no doubt...

742
01:20:51,256 --> 01:20:52,686
一定也在等船只
waiting for a ship.

743
01:20:53,956 --> 01:20:55,236
但是没有船来过
But no ship came.

744
01:20:57,866 --> 01:20:59,676
没有船会来
No ship is going to come.

745
01:21:00,626 --> 01:21:02,266
如果我们呆在这 我们会死
If we stay, we die.

746
01:21:03,086 --> 01:21:05,236
<i>你们觉得如果鸟儿过来看到
<i>How long do you think it would take to trust the birds

747
01:21:05,306 --> 01:21:07,846
<i>自己的蛋被吃了会多久不再过来
<i>to stop coming here once they see their eggs eaten?

748
01:21:26,616 --> 01:21:30,416
这是知道自己将要死去的好处
It's a privilege to know the moment of one's death in advance.

749
01:21:30,686 --> 01:21:32,476
可以为此准备
And to be able to prepare for it...

750
01:21:33,766 --> 01:21:36,756
离家太远的诅咒
a curse to be so far from home...

751
01:21:37,986 --> 01:21:42,216
或者有机会说再见但没机会和解
or a chance to say goodbyes, without a chance to make peace...

752
01:21:43,076 --> 01:21:45,366
或者报仇的机会
or a chance to settle scores.

753
01:21:48,316 --> 01:21:51,056
但是 我们之间清楚了
But alas, at least those are settled between us,

754
01:21:51,486 --> 01:21:52,916
船长
Cap'n?

755
01:21:54,856 --> 01:21:56,416
什么船长
Captain of what?

756
01:21:57,026 --> 01:21:59,346
埃塞克斯号沉没了不是你的责任
The Essex was lost and no fault o'yours.

757
01:21:59,946 --> 01:22:02,486
我该受谴责 你不是船长
- I was as much to blame... - You were not the Captain!

758
01:22:07,916 --> 01:22:10,216
你天生就是干这活的料
You were born to do this job.

759
01:22:11,056 --> 01:22:13,146
我只是生下来只能干这个
I was just born into it.

760
01:22:25,896 --> 01:22:27,896
我们干了什么 你觉得 乔治
What we do, do ya think, George?

761
01:22:29,526 --> 01:22:33,596
我们干了什么冒犯了上帝 让他这么不开心
What offense did we give God to upset him so?

762
01:22:33,646 --> 01:22:36,546
冒犯上帝的是那些白鲸
The only creature to have offended God here is the whale.

763
01:22:37,346 --> 01:22:38,536
不是我们
Not us?

764
01:22:40,446 --> 01:22:44,066
不是我们的傲慢 我们的贪婪 看我们现在在哪儿
Not our arrogance, our greed? Look where we find ourselves.

765
01:22:44,116 --> 01:22:46,646
我们是上帝按自己喜好创造出来的高级生物
We are supreme creatures made in God's own likeness.

766
01:22:48,046 --> 01:22:49,676
我们是地球上的主宰
We're earthly kings,

767
01:22:49,926 --> 01:22:53,726
我们要环航我们居住的星球
whose business it is to circumnavigate the planet bestowed to us.

768
01:22:54,316 --> 01:22:56,476
将自然屈服于我们的意志
And to bend nature to OUR will.

769
01:22:56,586 --> 01:23:00,146
我们经历了这么多你还觉得主宰一切吗
You really feel like an earthly king after everything that we've been through?

770
01:23:01,626 --> 01:23:06,116
我们什么都不是 我们是微粒 灰尘 但是我们
- We're nothing... we're specks... dust. - But we're...

771
01:23:07,136 --> 01:23:09,226
拂晓时朝太阳方向行驶
We sail into the sun at dawn.

772
01:23:10,556 --> 01:23:14,186
如果我们要死 死在上帝的光辉里
If we are to die, with God's grace.

773
01:23:15,196 --> 01:23:17,126
让我们像男人一样死去
Let us die as men.

774
01:23:28,506 --> 01:23:31,406
<i>我们准备好了吗 维克斯先生 是的 长官
<i>- Are we ready, Mr. Weeks? - Aye, Sir.

775
01:23:38,636 --> 01:23:40,326
查普尔先生
Mr. Chappel.

776
01:23:40,396 --> 01:23:42,996
莱特先生 我不能 长官
- Mr. Wright. - I can't do it, Sir.

777
01:23:44,136 --> 01:23:45,866
我 洛克斯 维克斯
Me, Locks and Weeks...

778
01:23:47,176 --> 01:23:48,656
我们留下来
we're stayin'.

779
01:23:57,176 --> 01:23:58,346
准备出发 马修
Ready to go, Matthew?

780
01:24:09,666 --> 01:24:12,286
我来帮你一把 有什么用
- I'll give you a hand here... - What's the point?

781
01:24:12,536 --> 01:24:14,676
你听见我说的吗 不 我们一起回家 一起回家
- You hear me? - No, we're goin' home, we're goin' home.

782
01:24:14,766 --> 01:24:16,146
没用的
There's no point.

783
01:24:16,956 --> 01:24:18,406
走吧
Just go.

784
01:24:22,216 --> 01:24:24,436
妈的 马修
God damn it, Matthew.

785
01:24:27,136 --> 01:24:28,536
没事的
It's all right.

786
01:24:29,506 --> 01:24:31,666
我回家立马派一艘船过来接你
I'll send a boat for you the minute we get back.

787
01:24:31,816 --> 01:24:34,116
然后我们回到楠塔基特玩牌 好吗
And we'll play cards back in Nantucket, all right?

788
01:24:34,746 --> 01:24:37,796
好 一言为定 好
- Yeah, it's a deal. - Good.

789
01:24:44,506 --> 01:24:46,426
你要我帮你打开水壶吗
You want me to open that for ya?

790
01:24:50,426 --> 01:24:52,576
我能行的
Naw, I think I'll manage.

791
01:24:58,736 --> 01:25:00,396
上帝保佑你 兄弟
God be with you, Brother.

792
01:25:02,206 --> 01:25:04,036
也保佑你
And you.

793
01:25:22,576 --> 01:25:24,286
彼得森
Brother Peterson?

794
01:25:25,926 --> 01:25:28,826
你一起跟我们走吧 彼得森先生
- Y'all comin' with us? - Mr. Peterson.

795
01:25:29,056 --> 01:25:31,626
和邦德一起登船走吧
Why don't you come on our boat with Mr. Bond.

796
01:25:59,056 --> 01:26:02,626
困住的第48天

797
01:26:04,626 --> 01:26:07,116
在哪儿 他在哪儿
Where... where is he?

798
01:26:08,216 --> 01:26:09,956
<i>波拉德
<i>Pollard.

799
01:26:10,736 --> 01:26:13,206
劳伦斯先生 劳伦斯先生 醒醒
Mr. Lawrence, Mr. Lawrence, wake up.

800
01:26:14,836 --> 01:26:16,856
<i>另一条船去哪儿了
<i>Where has the other boat gone?

801
01:26:17,326 --> 01:26:19,286
波拉德 波拉德 船长波拉德
- Pollard! Pollard! - Captain Pollard!

802
01:26:19,566 --> 01:26:22,296
波拉德 波拉德 船长波拉德
- Pollard! Pollard! - Cap'n Pollard!

803
01:26:22,476 --> 01:26:24,286
波拉德 船长
- Pollard! - Captain!

804
01:26:29,626 --> 01:26:31,206
<i>波拉德
<i>Pollard!

805
01:26:35,426 --> 01:26:36,976
休息会儿
Get some rest.

806
01:26:52,636 --> 01:26:54,846
本杰明 你在干什么
Benjamin, what are you doing?

807
01:26:54,896 --> 01:26:56,546
他死了
He's dead.

808
01:26:57,006 --> 01:26:58,756
把他丢海里 长官
Throwing him overboard, Sir.

809
01:27:00,536 --> 01:27:03,526
看着我 看着我 本杰明
Look at me, look at me Benjamin.

810
01:27:08,336 --> 01:27:12,466
没有理智的水手会丢弃也许会救自己一命的东西
No right minded sailor discards what might yet save him.

811
01:27:23,346 --> 01:27:25,676
听我说 孩子 听我说
Listen to me, Boy, listen to me.

812
01:27:29,716 --> 01:27:31,916
他能救我们
He can help us.

813
01:27:31,966 --> 01:27:34,306
<i>我的上帝 我们神圣的
<i>My God, our heavenly...

814
01:27:39,246 --> 01:27:42,786
<i>这些生物每日祈盼着食物
<i>Thy creatures wait On Thee for daily food.

815
01:28:00,026 --> 01:28:02,936
决定了
So it was decided.

816
01:28:08,996 --> 01:28:11,146
我们准备了尸体
We prepared the body.

817
01:28:14,056 --> 01:28:16,136
<i>我们去除了内脏
<i>We removed the organs.

818
01:28:18,776 --> 01:28:21,276
分割了他的四肢
Separated his limbs from his body.

819
01:28:22,876 --> 01:28:25,906
从骨头上切下了所有的肉
And cut all the flesh from the bones.

820
01:28:29,966 --> 01:28:31,746
<i>然后
<i>After which...

821
01:28:32,336 --> 01:28:34,256
我们拼起了尸块
we closed body.

822
01:28:35,716 --> 01:28:37,326
然后把尸体缝起来
And then we sewed it up...

823
01:28:37,616 --> 01:28:39,626
<i>尽我们所能
<i>as decently as we could...

824
01:28:40,136 --> 01:28:42,816
<i>然后扔到了海里
<i>and committed it to the sea.

825
01:28:44,506 --> 01:28:46,486
我们先吃了心脏
We ate the heart first.

826
01:28:55,006 --> 01:28:56,896
你有意见
You judge me.

827
01:28:58,616 --> 01:29:00,256
不
No.

828
01:29:06,286 --> 01:29:09,186
那个
There... there...

829
01:29:10,766 --> 01:29:11,846
说完了
it's done.

830
01:29:14,286 --> 01:29:16,106
<i>说完了
<i>It is out.

831
01:29:17,466 --> 01:29:19,236
你从未告诉过任何人
You never told anyone?

832
01:29:22,036 --> 01:29:23,116
没有
No.

833
01:29:24,756 --> 01:29:26,586
包括你的妻子
Not even your wife?

834
01:29:27,386 --> 01:29:29,976
你觉得如果她知道我做的罪孽
Do you think she could ever love me,

835
01:29:30,026 --> 01:29:32,926
她还会爱我吗
if she knew the abominations I had committed?

836
01:29:32,976 --> 01:29:35,846
不 她还会爱你的
Yes, she would.

837
01:29:36,536 --> 01:29:39,746
如果你和我相遇的时候告诉我
And if you had told me this story when we met,

838
01:29:40,566 --> 01:29:43,406
我今天还会是你的妻子
I would still wear your ring today.

839
01:29:45,116 --> 01:29:47,136
<i>那个男孩的勇敢
<i>The strength of that boy,

840
01:29:47,286 --> 01:29:49,576
还在你内心
still lives in you.

841
01:29:51,576 --> 01:29:53,456
我看得出
I see that...

842
01:29:54,066 --> 01:29:55,866
即使你自己不觉察
even if you don't.

843
01:30:17,146 --> 01:30:19,556
你可以说完你的故事了 亲爱的
You can finish your story now, My Love.

844
01:30:30,846 --> 01:30:32,246
<i>嘿
<i>Look...

845
01:30:35,626 --> 01:30:37,696
<i>坐起来
<i>Sit up.

846
01:30:40,296 --> 01:30:41,506
<i>听着
<i>Listen.

847
01:30:42,706 --> 01:30:44,106
<i>妈的
<i>Damn thing.

848
01:30:47,146 --> 01:30:49,536
<i>我们还有些水
<i>We still got a few drops of the water left.

849
01:30:49,756 --> 01:30:52,416
<i>别放弃 我们要回家了
<i>Don't ya quit on me, we're goin' home.

850
01:30:58,006 --> 01:30:59,756
你还有家人在吗
Do you have a family...

851
01:31:00,456 --> 01:31:02,296
查斯先生
back home, Mr. Chase?

852
01:31:02,326 --> 01:31:03,706
有的 我的妻子
Yeah, I have wife.

853
01:31:07,556 --> 01:31:09,996
对 还有一个儿子和一个女儿
Yes, and a son or a daughter.

854
01:31:23,556 --> 01:31:26,996
困住的第71天 南美以西1200海里

855
01:31:55,066 --> 01:31:57,896
好
Very well.

856
01:31:58,386 --> 01:32:00,186
船长 我们重新抽签
Cap'n, we'll draw again.

857
01:32:00,356 --> 01:32:02,666
我们不会这么做
We'll do no such thing.

858
01:32:03,596 --> 01:32:06,306
我们重新抽 拉姆斯德尔先生
- We'll draw again. - Mr. Ramsdell,

859
01:32:07,356 --> 01:32:10,246
你要用这枪来指挥
you will assume command of this vessel.

860
01:32:15,026 --> 01:32:16,166
你明白
Ya got that?

861
01:32:16,216 --> 01:32:19,506
你是我们的船长 你的船员需要你
You're our cap'n, your men need you.

862
01:32:20,606 --> 01:32:22,206
船员没事的
The men will be fine.

863
01:32:23,176 --> 01:32:26,616
拜托了 拜托了
Please. Please. Please.

864
01:32:26,986 --> 01:32:28,826
亨利 让我们再抽签
- Henry... - Let us go again.

865
01:32:29,586 --> 01:32:31,386
这是命令
It is an order.

866
01:32:32,626 --> 01:32:34,526
如果你做不到
If you cannot do it,

867
01:32:34,626 --> 01:32:36,916
把枪给其他人
pass the pistol to another man.

868
01:33:21,956 --> 01:33:24,246
<i>我们在赤道无风带几周了
<i>We were weeks in the Doldrums.

869
01:33:24,386 --> 01:33:27,136
<i>太平洋那片区域远比海洋枯竭
<i>That part of the Pacific is more desert than ocean.

870
01:33:27,866 --> 01:33:30,766
<i>太阳炙热
<i>The sun beating down...

871
01:33:30,806 --> 01:33:32,406
我害怕
My fear...

872
01:33:33,266 --> 01:33:35,226
我能想到的是
All I could think about...

873
01:33:36,756 --> 01:33:40,406
所有人都会死而我是最后一个活着的
was that everyone would die and I'd be the last left alive.

874
01:33:41,746 --> 01:33:46,336
查斯只知道我们离陆地还有800英里
Well, as best as Mr. Chase could tell, we were still 800 miles from land.

875
01:33:52,006 --> 01:33:53,456
<i>查斯先生
<i>Mr. Chase.

876
01:34:01,506 --> 01:34:03,296
船长波拉德
Cap'n Pollard.

877
01:34:05,576 --> 01:34:07,536
很高兴见到你
Very happy to see you.

878
01:34:08,106 --> 01:34:10,936
我们生存下来没什么值得高兴
Very little happiness in our survival.

879
01:34:12,296 --> 01:34:15,176
我们也是 长官
Nor in ours, Sir.

880
01:34:15,436 --> 01:34:17,036
巴尔齐莱号
Barzillai?

881
01:34:19,676 --> 01:34:21,026
另一艘船
The third boat?

882
01:34:22,276 --> 01:34:26,756
<i>他们不见了 几天不见了
<i>They're gone, they've been gone for days.

883
01:34:26,986 --> 01:34:29,406
<i>我估计他们迷失了 长官
<i>I'm afraid they're lost, Sir.

884
01:34:59,066 --> 01:35:01,856
<i>查斯先生 你为这个准备好了
<i>Mr. Chase, you are prepared for this.

885
01:35:17,966 --> 01:35:19,946
不过是头白鲸
It's just a whale.

886
01:35:23,706 --> 01:35:25,556
那里 投茅
There! Throw the lance!

887
01:35:26,626 --> 01:35:27,606
<i>投啊
<i>Throw it!

888
01:35:31,696 --> 01:35:34,456
<i>投啊
<i>Throw it, drown the lad!

889
01:35:45,636 --> 01:35:48,316
<i>投啊
<i>Throw it!

890
01:35:57,156 --> 01:36:01,626
<i>就是现在 投茅啊
<i>Do it! Now! Throw the lance!

891
01:36:19,506 --> 01:36:22,096
<i>你为什么不投
<i>Why didn't you throw it?

892
01:36:48,116 --> 01:36:49,936
你他妈是个傻子
You're a damn fool.

893
01:37:13,036 --> 01:37:15,906
<i>洋流把我们拆散了
<i>The current drew us apart...

894
01:37:16,796 --> 01:37:20,366
<i>那是我们最后一次见到船长波拉德的鲸船
<i>and that was the last we would see of Captain Pollard's whale boat.

895
01:37:21,796 --> 01:37:23,066
困住的第87天

896
01:37:23,106 --> 01:37:25,326
一艘船
A boat!

897
01:37:25,536 --> 01:37:27,746
<i>前方有一艘船
<i>A boat on the forward bow!

898
01:37:53,156 --> 01:37:55,096
上帝仁慈
May god have mercy.

899
01:38:08,156 --> 01:38:11,096
困住的第90天 1821年2月18日

900
01:38:37,636 --> 01:38:39,216
查斯先生
Mr. Chase.

901
01:38:42,346 --> 01:38:44,406
父亲
Father...

902
01:38:46,056 --> 01:38:48,496
别丢下我 父亲
don't leave me, Father.

903
01:39:38,256 --> 01:39:40,396
嘿 长官
Hey, Sir.

904
01:39:41,036 --> 01:39:45,346
查斯先生 长官 看 看 长官
Mr. Chase. Sir. Look. Look, Sir.

905
01:39:49,006 --> 01:39:50,006
长官
Sir.

906
01:39:50,856 --> 01:39:53,106
看 那里
Look. Out there.

907
01:39:53,446 --> 01:39:54,816
他们来了
They're coming.

908
01:39:58,806 --> 01:40:01,216
他们来救我们了
They're coming for us.

909
01:40:23,096 --> 01:40:28,186
<i>我们在那里被救了
<i>We were rescued there, off the Isle of Mбs Afuera, Chile,

910
01:40:28,986 --> 01:40:32,036
<i>埃塞克斯号沉船90天后
<i>ninety days after the sinking of the Essex.

911
01:40:33,396 --> 01:40:37,506
<i>他们给我们一些衣服和皮革吃
<i>They gave us some old clothes... leathers, too.

912
01:40:38,376 --> 01:40:42,366
<i>起先感觉很难吃
<i>It was hard to eat at first... strange.

913
01:40:43,406 --> 01:40:45,196
<i>他们尽力照顾我们
<i>They looked after us as best they could,

914
01:40:45,296 --> 01:40:48,496
<i>然后他们找到了可以带我们回家的一艘船
<i>then we found a ship that could carry us home.

915
01:40:49,336 --> 01:40:52,506
<i>回家又花了三个月
<i>That voyage took another three months.

916
01:40:53,336 --> 01:40:55,506
1821年6月11日 楠塔基特港口

917
01:41:00,696 --> 01:41:04,176
<i>全岛的人好像都过来看我们回来
<i>It looked like the whole Island turned out to see us return.

918
01:41:05,396 --> 01:41:09,716
<i>但是没有欢呼 只有沉寂
<i>But there were no cheers... only silence.

919
01:41:11,266 --> 01:41:17,106
<i>他们看我们的样子像是看到鬼 幽灵
<i>They looked at us like we were... apparitions... phantoms.

920
01:41:17,806 --> 01:41:22,066
<i>我们没有对任何人说起我们生存的细节
<i>We'd said nothing of the details of our survival to anyone.

921
01:41:22,126 --> 01:41:26,166
<i>但是我猜他们知道我们的困境
<i>But I wondered if they somehow knew of our privations.

922
01:41:27,316 --> 01:41:29,546
<i>也许他们只是好奇
<i>Maybe they were just curious.

923
01:42:17,136 --> 01:42:19,116
我保证过的 不是吗
I promised, didn't I?

924
01:42:27,576 --> 01:42:28,706
天啊
God.

925
01:42:31,956 --> 01:42:34,386
嘿 宝贝 你是谁啊
Hey, Sweetie! Who is this?

926
01:42:35,146 --> 01:42:37,116
菲比安
Phebe Ann.

927
01:42:41,096 --> 01:42:42,936
菲比安·查斯
Phebe Ann Chase.

928
01:42:43,996 --> 01:42:45,826
他是你的父亲
It's your Daddy.

929
01:42:47,416 --> 01:42:49,256
嘿 宝贝
Hey, Sweetie.

930
01:42:53,996 --> 01:42:56,426
他是你的父亲
It's your Daddy.

931
01:43:13,266 --> 01:43:15,506
<i>当然还是有人找上他
<i>Of course they couldn't leave him alone.

932
01:43:15,776 --> 01:43:18,716
<i>查斯先生和他的妻子往家走了不久
<i>Mr. Chase and his wife had scarcely walked a block towards home

933
01:43:18,796 --> 01:43:21,946
他就被拦下来并带回了海事办公室
when he was stopped and made to return to the Maritime Office.

934
01:43:23,406 --> 01:43:26,146
<i>生意上的事还有疑问
<i>There were business matters still in question.

935
01:43:40,116 --> 01:43:41,776
对于这件事
So, to the matter...

936
01:43:46,176 --> 01:43:49,676
因为我们此次航线造成了巨大的人员和财产损失
Due to the significant loss of life and property on our voyage,

937
01:43:50,186 --> 01:43:52,676
将会有一场听证会
it seems there will be an inquiry.

938
01:43:53,136 --> 01:43:57,576
作为船长和大副 我们需要交待事实经过
And, as Captain and first mate, we will be expected to give account of what happened.

939
01:43:58,026 --> 01:43:59,356
是的 当然
Yes, of course.

940
01:43:59,416 --> 01:44:04,096
我就这件事和船主和我父亲讨论过
And, having discussed this with the ship owners and... my father,

941
01:44:05,106 --> 01:44:08,686
显然完全交待经过会有后果
it is clear that full disclosure will have ramifications...

942
01:44:09,336 --> 01:44:12,176
对整个行业有可怕的后果
terrible ramifications for whole industry.

943
01:44:13,126 --> 01:44:15,626
一头白鲸弄沉了埃塞克斯号
That a whale brought down the Essex.

944
01:44:16,656 --> 01:44:18,946
但这是事实
But it's the truth.

945
01:44:26,106 --> 01:44:29,996
如果保险商和投资人开始担心
If the insurance houses and investors were to start worrying about...

946
01:44:30,076 --> 01:44:32,976
海怪把船弄沉
sea monsters sinking ships,

947
01:44:33,296 --> 01:44:36,036
水手们很难活下来
sailors drawing lots to survive...

948
01:44:37,266 --> 01:44:40,866
我们在石油行业 所有人
We are in the oil business... all of us.

949
01:44:41,496 --> 01:44:46,996
在任何一个行业成功的机率一定要比失败的风险要高
And as in any business the probability of success must always be greater the risk incurred.

950
01:44:48,786 --> 01:44:50,656
那么 你有什么建议 乔治
So, what are you suggesting, George?

951
01:44:50,886 --> 01:44:53,096
你就说船搁浅了
That you say that the ship ran aground.

952
01:44:54,266 --> 01:44:56,976
那是个谎言 并且说船员是淹死的
- That's a lie. - And that the men that died drowned.

953
01:44:57,406 --> 01:44:58,186
那也是个谎言
That's another lie.

954
01:44:58,236 --> 01:45:00,186
想想吧 他们会让你当船长
Think on it... they will make you captain.

955
01:45:00,226 --> 01:45:02,496
那个我是有书面保证的
Oh! That pledge I already have in writing.

956
01:45:02,606 --> 01:45:06,606
<i>那个前提是你带回一船的鲸油
<i>Only on the condition you bring home a ship full of oil.

957
01:45:07,866 --> 01:45:09,546
这么做会确保你这件事
This way it's guaranteed.

958
01:45:09,746 --> 01:45:12,036
你会变成有钱人
You would be a wealthy man.

959
01:45:12,176 --> 01:45:16,476
查斯不再是陆人的名字 而是有记录的
The name Chase need no longer be a landsman's name, but an established name

960
01:45:16,506 --> 01:45:20,026
属于楠塔基特岛伟大家族的名字
that belongs among the great families of Nantucket.

961
01:45:20,806 --> 01:45:23,366
你要我为了功名掩盖发生的一切
You want me to whitewash what happened for profit?

962
01:45:24,066 --> 01:45:27,246
我们是要你务实些
We're asking you to be pragmatic.

963
01:45:42,746 --> 01:45:45,556
埃塞克斯号是被一头白鲸撞沉的
The Essex was stoved by a white whale.

964
01:45:46,036 --> 01:45:48,866
我们幸存下来的在装备不良的捕鲸船上
And those of us that survived in ill-equipped whale boats

965
01:45:48,936 --> 01:45:53,106
只能靠犯下罪孽才能存活
had to commit abominations in order to survive.

966
01:45:53,266 --> 01:45:57,406
我们回来后 又被指望传播公然露骨的谎言
And on our return, we're expected to spread barefaced lies,

967
01:45:57,766 --> 01:46:00,916
好让你们这些楠塔基特岛岛船主们
so that you, the ship owners of Nantucket,

968
01:46:01,376 --> 01:46:04,286
赚钱晚上再睡得安稳觉吗
might line your pockets and sleep well at night?

969
01:46:05,406 --> 01:46:08,876
我不会掩盖真相
Well, I will not embroil the truth.

970
01:46:08,926 --> 01:46:10,756
乔治 你也不应该
Nor should you, George.

971
01:46:30,266 --> 01:46:32,126
<i>我最后一次见他
<i>That last time I saw him...

972
01:46:32,466 --> 01:46:33,876
查斯先生 长官
Mr. Chase, Sir.

973
01:46:34,316 --> 01:46:37,876
<i>我说不出我想说的话
<i>I couldn't find the right words to say what I wanted.

974
01:46:38,736 --> 01:46:40,016
汤姆斯
Thomas.

975
01:46:41,006 --> 01:46:42,776
<i>也许我没什么想说的
<i>Perhaps there ARE no words.

976
01:46:45,176 --> 01:46:48,196
我 我要去法尔茅斯了
I'm... I'm gonna be on my way to Falmouth, and...

977
01:46:51,326 --> 01:46:52,986
那个
it's...

978
01:46:53,116 --> 01:46:55,426
那个 很荣幸 长官
it's... it's been an honor, Sir,

979
01:46:55,746 --> 01:46:57,566
能够服务于您
to serve with you.

980
01:47:00,826 --> 01:47:03,636
是我的荣幸 尼克森先生
The honor has been mine, Mr. Nickerson.

981
01:47:20,816 --> 01:47:22,536
拿着
Take it.

982
01:47:27,096 --> 01:47:28,996
祝你好运 汤姆斯
Good luck out there, Thomas.

983
01:47:30,106 --> 01:47:31,806
谢谢 长官
Thank you, Sir.

984
01:48:00,696 --> 01:48:03,986
第二天乔治·波拉德被召唤到听证会
Next day George Pollard was called before the inquiry.

985
01:48:08,526 --> 01:48:10,866
先生们 船长乔治·波拉德
Gentlemen, Captain George Pollard.

986
01:48:11,406 --> 01:48:13,976
<i>楠塔基特所有重要人物都在那儿
<i>All the important men of Nantucket were there...

987
01:48:14,956 --> 01:48:17,306
<i>这是惯例
<i>it was a formality.

988
01:48:17,906 --> 01:48:20,296
<i>日安 船长 请坐
<i>Good day to you, Captain, please sit down.

989
01:48:25,876 --> 01:48:27,676
<i>事实是
<i>For the record then.

990
01:48:29,506 --> 01:48:35,126
埃塞克斯号是在厄瓜多尔以西被一头1200多米长的白鲸撞沉的
The Essex was stoved by a white whale 12 hundred meters west of Ecuador.

991
01:48:35,196 --> 01:48:38,226
就像欧文·查斯说的那样
It was as if Owen Chase himself had spoken.

992
01:48:39,896 --> 01:48:42,006
他告诉了他们真相
He told them the truth.

993
01:48:45,366 --> 01:48:47,956
<i>船长波拉德的良心发现了
<i>Cap'n Pollard's conscience was clear...

994
01:48:49,066 --> 01:48:51,526
<i>但那场听证会是个耻辱
<i>but the inquiry was a sham.

995
01:48:53,016 --> 01:48:55,456


996
01:48:57,506 --> 01:49:01,486
至于那头白鲸 他们再也没有找到
over the white whale... they never found it.

997
01:49:02,776 --> 01:49:05,706
<i>他再一次出航但在夏威夷搁浅
<i>He ran a second ship aground off of Hawaii...

998
01:49:06,816 --> 01:49:08,036
<i>两次诅咒
<i>twice cursed.

999
01:49:09,626 --> 01:49:11,306
再也没有出航过
Never sailed again.

1000
01:49:11,556 --> 01:49:13,206
欧文·查斯
And Owen Chase?

1001
01:49:14,306 --> 01:49:16,346
他说到做到
He was a man of his word.

1002
01:49:16,776 --> 01:49:19,746
他派了一艘船去了杜斯特岛
First, he sent a boat back to Ducie Island.

1003
01:49:20,816 --> 01:49:22,656
花花公子已经死了
Mr. Joy had passed...

1004
01:49:22,916 --> 01:49:26,426
但是其他人居然还都活着
but the other three were incredibly still alive.

1005
01:49:29,276 --> 01:49:30,546
然后呢
And then?

1006
01:49:31,066 --> 01:49:34,666
他带着家人搬到了新贝德福德
Then he packed up his family and moved to New Bedford...

1007
01:49:36,656 --> 01:49:38,286
<i>去重新开始生活
<i>to start over...

1008
01:49:38,766 --> 01:49:40,806
<i>在一家商店
<i>in a merchant...

1009
01:49:41,066 --> 01:49:43,456
<i>完成自己的人生旅程
<i>sailing his own terms.

1010
01:49:52,676 --> 01:49:56,146
<i>你用钱换到故事了 梅尔维尔先生
<i>Well, you certainly got your money's worth, Mr. Melville.

1011
01:49:56,396 --> 01:49:58,786
这二月的夜晚真是一年中最漫长的
These February nights are the longest of the year.

1012
01:49:59,076 --> 01:50:02,136
你们都可以休息了 我不行
- Well, you can both rest now. - Leave me...

1013
01:50:02,446 --> 01:50:05,316
我还有一段时间不能休息
I shall not be resting for some time.

1014
01:50:05,566 --> 01:50:06,996
<i>为什么
<i>Why?

1015
01:50:07,716 --> 01:50:12,886
你得到了你的故事 情节都有了
Ya got your story there, and your plot is all there.

1016
01:50:12,936 --> 01:50:16,666
也许我想要的不是情节
Maybe it wasn't a plot I was after.

1017
01:50:16,816 --> 01:50:18,876
不是 那是什么
No, what then?

1018
01:50:19,056 --> 01:50:21,556
你今晚给我的其他东西
Something else you've given me tonight.

1019
01:50:21,606 --> 01:50:23,116
是什么
What is that?

1020
01:50:23,696 --> 01:50:28,386
敢于去别人不敢去的地方的勇气
The courage to go where... one does not want to go.

1021
01:50:29,806 --> 01:50:31,646
梅尔维尔先生
Mr. Melville,

1022
01:50:31,936 --> 01:50:34,986
你听到的 我告诉你的
what you've heard, what I've told you,

1023
01:50:37,666 --> 01:50:42,156
是否都会成为你书中的一部分
will it all be of service to your book?

1024
01:50:43,246 --> 01:50:46,846
这会是部虚构的小说 尼克森先生
It will be a work of fiction, Mr. Nickerson,

1025
01:50:47,996 --> 01:50:49,916
受真实事件启发
inspired by truth,

1026
01:50:51,036 --> 01:50:54,636
但我不觉得我会用全部事实
but I don't believe I'll feel the need to use all of it.

1027
01:51:03,396 --> 01:51:04,726
谢谢 给
- Thank you. - Here...

1028
01:51:05,206 --> 01:51:06,416
拿着这个
take that with you.

1029
01:51:06,476 --> 01:51:08,826
不 钱是给你的 我坚持
No, the money is for you, I insist.

1030
01:51:09,986 --> 01:51:11,226
我坚持你要收下
I insist you keep it.

1031
01:51:11,566 --> 01:51:16,116
我坚持这谈话里还是有一个人是清醒的
And I insist that one person in this conversation is sober.

1032
01:51:26,266 --> 01:51:29,286
该回马萨诸塞州皮茨菲尔德了
So, it's back to Pittsfield, Massachusetts.

1033
01:51:29,816 --> 01:51:32,376
祝你好运
Well, good luck.

1034
01:51:33,486 --> 01:51:34,746
谢谢
Thank you.

1035
01:51:38,186 --> 01:51:39,616
你知道吗
Ya know...

1036
01:51:39,946 --> 01:51:43,816
<i>我听说宾夕法尼亚州一个人最近在地上钻了一个洞
<i>I heard a man from Pennsylvania drilled a hole in the ground recently,

1037
01:51:44,596 --> 01:51:46,326
发现了油
and found oil.

1038
01:51:46,796 --> 01:51:48,636
不会是真的吧
That can't be true.

1039
01:51:49,116 --> 01:51:50,636
我也听说过
I heard it, too.

1040
01:51:52,436 --> 01:51:55,456
地上的油
Oil from ground.

1041
01:51:56,566 --> 01:51:59,006
真想不到
Fancy that.

1042
01:52:29,566 --> 01:52:38,006
赫尔曼·梅尔维尔 1850年完成了他的小说

1043
01:52:41,566 --> 01:52:48,006
一年后白鲸记发表

1044
01:52:50,566 --> 01:52:58,006
对于白鲸记纳撒尼尔·霍桑盛赞它会成为美国伟大的作品


